				</common:classification>
			</classificationInformation>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Nitrogenous fertilizer is a natural or artificial substance containing chemical elements that improve plant growth and productivity. It enhances the natural fertility of the soil or replaces chemical elements taken from the soil by previous crops. The industry includes the production of synthetic ammonia, nitric acid, ammonium nitrate, and urea. These are used primarily as intermediates in the production of ammonium nitrate and urea fertilizers. Nitrogenous fertilizers are geared towards producing leaves and foliage.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">氮肥是一种天然或人工物质，含有能改善植物生长和提高产量的化学元素。它能提高土壤的天然肥力，或替代前茬作物从土壤中吸收的化学元素。该行业包括合成氨、硝酸、硝酸铵和尿素的生产。这些产品主要用作硝酸铵和尿素肥料生产的中间体。氮肥主要用于生产叶子和叶片。</common:generalComment>
